    <h1>Gutter Cleaning in Surrey — A Dry Home and Peace of Mind All Year Round</h1>

    <p>Residents of Surrey face the same situation every year: in autumn, gutters fill with maple and oak leaves, cedar and fir needles, seeds, and small branches. In winter, moss begins to grow rapidly in the constantly wet channels. In spring, pollen and fresh plant debris add to the buildup. And in the Lower Mainland, the rain can be so persistent it sometimes feels endless. As a result, water stops flowing through the downspouts and instead spills down the façade, behind siding, and toward the foundation. This often triggers a chain reaction: stains → mold → rot → basement dampness → extremely costly repairs.</p>

    <p>We help Surrey homeowners avoid exactly this scenario. People who already have mortgages, children, retirement plans, and a clear understanding that it is far better to invest in prevention today than to pay five to ten times more for major repairs later.</p>

    <h2>Why do gutters in Surrey require attention more often than in many other BC cities?</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>A large number of tall trees in residential areas (especially in Newton, Fleetwood, Cloverdale, Panorama Ridge, Fraser Heights, Grandview Heights)</li>
        <li>Proximity to major parks and green spaces: Green Timbers, Tynehead, Surrey Bend, Hjorth Road Park, Hawthorne Park</li>
        <li>A long wet season: November through March with very few dry days, plus high humidity year‑round</li>
        <li>Typical housing from the 1980s–2000s with wooden fascia, soffits, and siding that are highly vulnerable to constant moisture</li>
        <li>Many homes built on slopes or in low‑lying areas where water accumulates around foundations very quickly</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What our professional gutter cleaning in Surrey includes:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Complete manual removal of debris from gutters — everything is taken out by hand and with specialized brushes (nothing is forced into the downspouts)</li>
        <li>Pressure rinsing only after manual cleaning is complete</li>
        <li>Full inspection of downspouts along their entire length — from roofline to ground, including elbows, connectors, and hidden sections</li>
        <li>Water flow testing to confirm the system is working properly</li>
        <li>Inspection of fascia, soffits, and adjacent areas for early signs of water damage</li>
        <li>Protection of your property: tarps for lawns and flower beds, padded ladder supports, and no mess left on walkways</li>
        <li>All debris removed from the site the same day</li>
        <li>Before‑and‑after photos of each side of the home (sent via WhatsApp, email, or messenger)</li>
        <li>Fixed pricing confirmed after inspection or from roof photos/videos — no surprise charges on site</li>
        <li>Workmanship guarantee of 60–120 days depending on the season</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who we help most often:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Families aged 35–50 who want their home to remain in good condition for the next 25–30 years</li>
        <li>Homeowners aged 55+ who no longer feel safe climbing ladders in wet conditions</li>
        <li>Owners of homes built between 1985 and 2005, which commonly have moisture‑sensitive roofline components</li>
        <li>Landlords of duplexes, triplexes, townhouses, and small rental properties</li>
        <li>Anyone who has already experienced a leak or mold issue and wants to prevent it from happening again</li>
    </ul>

